There is extensive construction going on at Les Halles behind the hotel, and the neighborhood can get a bit drunken and rowdy, so our room overlooking the courtyard was ideally quiet.	Only problem for some people might be a bit of noise at night due to the closeness of bars and noisy teenagers drunk outside at 6 in the morning.	We had a room overlooking the courtyard, view was nothing great but nice and quiet, even managed to sleep with the window open and enjoy the warm spring Paris air.